      "writtenOn": "2020-08-19T00:55:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes this is a security concern on both Fuchsia and Android. We map the whole pages to guest and both systems don\u0027t have access control of memory within a single page, it\u0027s possible for guest to tamper with host memory not bound to the host-mapped image.\n\nWe might want to do this for non-external host-visible memory in VkDecoderGlobalState.cpp as well -- maybe a later CL to address this.",
